In the SEM analysis results, not only the direct effect of RUP on SDGs was explored, but also its indirect effect (Table 2
                     , Fig. 8
                     ). The direct effect of RUP on SDG8 (decent work and economic growth) was the most significant (0.60), and SDG8 advancement realizes the economic growth, which leads to the related industrial chain development of MSW resource treatment, improves the economic benefits and job opportunities (Mubeen and Buekens, 2019). RUP indirectly affects SDG1 (poverty eradication) (0.23) through SDG8, and MSW resource utilization industry development brings more employment opportunities and income sources for the poor groups. RUP has the second largest direct impact on SDG17 (global partnership) (0.43), and MSW resource utilization technology improvement requires international exchanges to make continuous progress, thus promoting foreign funds and talent introduction (Almanaseer et al., 2020). RUP indirectly affects SDG10 (reduce inequality) (0.45) through SDG17, which may be because RUP reduces MSW resource waste and increases social and environmental justice. However, there is a negative direct effect of RUP on SDG13 (climate change) (-0.28). This is because WtE technology has not yet been popularized in China, and the waste disposal methods of incineration and landfill are used in most areas, which have negative impacts on the ecosystem, such as landfill waste occupying ecological land. Previous studies have shown that WtE technology does not reduce GHG emissions, which is also a possible reason (Shadbahr et al., 2022). Another negative direct impact of the RUP is on SDG15 (ecosystem) (-0.14), due to the potential to develop the RUP, which would increase land use for the construction of the WtE plant, with impacts on the ecosystem and environment (VaverkovÃ¡, 2019).
